<p><code>ListView</code> having TextView as its ListItem</p>  <pre><code>&lt;?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?&gt; &lt;LinearLayout xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"     android:layout_width="match_parent"     android:layout_height="wrap_content"     android:background="@android:color/transparent"&gt;      &lt;com.dexterous.genero15.font.Audiowide_Regular         android:id="@+id/club_name"         android:layout_width="match_parent"         android:layout_height="wrap_content"         android:capitalize="characters"         android:gravity="center"         android:minHeight="70dp"         android:padding="8dp" /&gt;  &lt;/LinearLayout&gt; </code></pre>  <p><code>Audiowide_Regular</code> is child of <code>AutofitTextView</code> which is child of <code>TextView</code></p>  <p>and listview having <code>setOnItemClickListener</code> on it.</p>  <p>If i removed attribute         <code>android:capitalize="characters"</code> from listItem then <code>onItemClick</code> works fine else <code>onItemClick</code> not executed.</p>  <p>Is there an dependency of <code>setOnItemClickListener</code> and         <code>android:capitalize="characters"</code> ?</p>